ublished in 1983, accounts for the many new works written by Carter since 1980 and accommodates the burgeoning critical literature on his music. Its features include many musical examples and a selected discography. In addition to the new foreword, the composer has provided his listing of three-to-six note chords and a note on "Voyage."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aArt History. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aMusical Arts & Ethnomusicology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171836640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501718366423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501718366/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles